    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-09-21T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-09-21T16:00:00-05:00" n="230"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d230">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/2309: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia (<persName corresp="#p_CJ1"
                            type="from">Caffery</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-21T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >September 21, 1932—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>74. <persName corresp="#p_OHE1">Olaya</persName> referring to telegram of
                    September 20 from <persName corresp="#p_LTF1">Lozano</persName>, Washington, and
                    his reply thereto, same date, regarding Argentine plans to take Chaco question
                    to Geneva, asks if the Department of State desires him only to instruct
                    Colombian delegates or should he also endeavor to persuade other Latin American
                    governments to instruct their delegates also.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
